tldr: The user requested a thorough aesthetic review and improvement of their
  sleep questionnaire app. The app's visual design was transformed with a
  calming sleep-themed palette, redesigned layouts, and polished components, and
  a console error related to null input values was fixed.
overview: The user initiated a request to elevate the aesthetic appeal of their
  sleep questionnaire application. The process began with a detailed analysis of
  the existing design, identifying areas such as the generic color palette,
  basic form elements, and lack of visual personality. The solution involved a
  comprehensive overhaul, introducing a calming, sleep-themed color palette with
  deep indigos, purples, and teal accents. Key components like the main form
  layout, progress bar, welcome screen, and individual form fields (checkboxes,
  radio buttons, sliders) were redesigned for a more polished and interactive
  user experience. Consistent theming was applied across all questionnaire
  sections, replacing old gray boxes with refined card-style groupings.
  Additionally, a console error related to  values being passed to input
  elements was diagnosed and fixed by implementing a safe value conversion in
  the  component. The overall outcome is an application with a
  significantly improved, cohesive, and professional aesthetic, tailored to a
  sleep health context, and free of the identified console error.
